The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 Team India get a feel of army life

Bangalore: Team India was on Monday given a feel of the army life when they visited the training centre of the elite parachute regiment located on the outskirts of the city. 

The players were given an overview of the parachute regiment and an opportunity to handle some of the weapons and equipment used by the Army, including a chance to check out their marksmanship and grenade throwing abilities. 

They also experienced first hand the rigorous training that volunteer aspirants for the special forces go through ? such as rock climbing, commando slide and advanced obstacles, an official release said. 

 The Indian team also underwent a tactical exercise in which they infiltrated into hostile territory to carry out a strike against a terrorist camp and rescued hostages. 

A short interaction with the officers and their families was also held during which the team presented cricket sets. 

The aim of the visit, said Brig Deepak Sinha, Commandant of the parachute regiment training centre, was to give the team an exposure to the army way of life and also a chance to interact with jawans. 

